cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new data structure called Sliding Bloom Filter and analyzes its time and memory requirements. 
2. cs.DB (Databases) - Bloom filters are commonly used in databases for approximate membership queries and the paper proposes a new variant of it. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - Bloom filters are related to information theory and the paper discusses the error probability of the Sliding Bloom Filter. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Bloom filters have applications in cryptography and security and the paper discusses the error probability of the Sliding Bloom Filter. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - Bloom filters are commonly used in distributed systems and the paper proposes a new variant of it that can be useful in distributed settings.
